<subSubSection id="C304FCE6761AFFDC69901E2F103CFE42" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA1AF6D761AFFDC69901E2F103CFE42" blockId="21.[151,1437,151,487]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC69901E2F135DFEE9" bold="true" box="[197,320,306,332]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE761AFFDC68121E2F1038FEEE" box="[327,549,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC68121E2F1038FEEE" box="[327,549,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hemipenthes curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC6BEF1E2F11F4FEEE" box="[698,1001,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE761AFFDC6BEF1E2F1133FEEE" box="[698,814,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celeris">H. celeris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE761AFFDC6A6C1E2F11F4FEEE" box="[825,1001,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">H. martinorum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE761AFFDC6D721E2F16AEFEEE" box="[1063,1203,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleuralis">
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC6D721E2F16AEFEEE" box="[1063,1203,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as all these species have the same genital structure and similar wing pigmentation, with a smooth color margin, not sinuous as in the other species in the genus. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE761AFFDC68AE1E9D10C4FE3C" box="[507,729,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC68AE1E9D10C4FE3C" box="[507,729,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hemipenthes curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from these species by the lack of color in cell 
<emphasis id="B96A737F761AFFDC6CD31E9D1788FE3C" box="[1414,1429,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">a</emphasis>
. This species is distributed in the Nearctic and Neotropical regions, with its most northern limit in California, Arizona, New 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD761AFFDC68161ED01381FE42" box="[323,412,461,487]" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Texas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
